title: 21 a Magyar étterem
speciality: Nagyon hangulatos környezetet biztosít a vár, panoráma nincs.
english: Mark 21 for its good cooking and a lovely view of the Castle, the cobbled streets and ancient houses of this historic district. This is a modern bistro type restaurant in an old Austro-Hungarian Monarchy setting. Some of the food is light, but the ravenous are sure to find several substantial main courses, as well. Classic, high quality Hungarian dishes and truly creative bistro creations are realised to a good or even excellent standard.  A long and excellent wine lists adds that special touch.

title: Aranypatkó Vendéglő
speciality: arany-patko.hu -- töröltem, nem működik a holnap!! RH
english: This is a pleasant restaurant in the side of the castle hill on the main square of Szigliget with a vast terrace, some of which offers a view of the lake. They have a traditional restaurant menu with a noticeable striving for innovation. Their dishes are steadily and dependably good in all essential respects – textures, harmonies and raw materials leaven o room for complaint. If only all 'traditional Hungarian kitchens' were like this! The wine list contains items from known Hungarian wineries. Service is attentive and quick.

title: Atakám Budai Bisztró és Étterem
english: Right at the foot of Castle Hill, this is an airy bistro with large windows and tables outside in summer time. Its loyal camp of regulars includes several chefs. Atakám has a simple menu which features partly plain Hungarian classics and partly some individual creations. Whichever category, the dishes are prepared with care and gusto from excellent raw material. Lovely fresh bread, tasty soups, juicy meats, dishes with honest, good, harmonious flavours including a number of really special and delightful creations are served by the owner in an attentive, competent fashion. The halászlé is one of the best in town.

title: Bajai Halászcsárda
speciality:
kerthelység, cigányzene

Nyáron nagy, virágos kerthelyiség, hétvégente hegedűs-szintis nótaszó. Nyaranta vasárnap 20 óráig van nyitva az étterem.
english: A large eatery in a shady garden by the cogwheel railway line – it has a rich Hungarian rustic feel to it with all the usual fish-restaurant fixtures. A good place to go for a really good classic Hungarian fish soup (halászlé). Within a rich array of fish dishes, those with carp or catfish are always made from fresh raw material while other fish dishes betray the deep freezer or, worse still, the muddy fish pond. The standard of other dishes sometimes gives at the knee, desserts could do with more devoted attention. Service is competent.

title: Bakos Attila családi vendéglője
english: A plain, no-nonsense menu steering the safe side of the culinary art, although the kitchen does feature a few of their own creations, too. Using local raw materials and traditional techniques, they offer a narrow and reliable range of the well-known national classics. The dishes are indeed authentic, flavourful and enjoyable in their own simple way. Service is friendly and direct.
